The W three C's C S S Working Group published C S S one defining basic styling,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
fonts, colors, spacing, then C S S two adding layout features like absolute positioning and media types. However,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
full C S S two proved ambitious,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
browser interoperability lagged,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
and parts of C S S two were later removed or deferred.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
C S S two one emerged as a refinement,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
focusing on what implementations agreed on,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
it became a W three C Recommendation in two thousand eleven after a decade of revisions.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
This long stabilization period gave browsers time to catch up,

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
and by two thousand eleven,

